        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer596129292" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10036213833047302950">Reading this book for me is akin to witnessing a train wreck. And I&apos;m only half-joking. You feel giddy, sick, want it to stop and yet you can&apos;t look away. You know the outcome is going to be bad, but you can&apos;t stop turning the pages to know what happens next. And you don&apos;t know what exactly the pull or the allure is about this book. The characters are mostly broken to the core and can hardly be saved. It&apos;s like a wretched hand which grabs you and pulls you down into the deep darkness of the tort</span>
  <span id="freeText10036213833047302950" style="display:none">Reading this book for me is akin to witnessing a train wreck. And I'm only half-joking. You feel giddy, sick, want it to stop and yet you can't look away. You know the outcome is going to be bad, but you can't stop turning the pages to know what happens next. And you don't know what exactly the pull or the allure is about this book. The characters are mostly broken to the core and can hardly be saved. It's like a wretched hand which grabs you and pulls you down into the deep darkness of the tortured souls.<br /><br />Honest opinion: Do I like the story? No. Do I like the characters? No. Do I find the book highly captivating for some reason? A definite yes.</span>
